{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636090","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636090"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:23:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:23:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17561"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17561","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17561"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.04,0.08,0.14,0.74]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10251"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71594"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10251","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10251"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17561"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57090"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7018"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23959"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24151"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71594"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe female breast receives its arterial blood supply from multiple sources that form an anastomotic network around and within the breast tissue.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following arteries provides the main blood supply to the medial aspect of the breast?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Posterior intercostal arteries","Thoracoacromial artery","Superior thoracic artery","Lateral thoracic artery","Internal thoracic artery"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Einternal thoracic artery\u003C/strong\u003E provides the main blood supply to the medial aspect of the breast through perforating branches. These branches pierce through the intercostal spaces to supply the medial breast tissue.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior intercostal arteries\u003C/strong\u003E contribute to breast blood supply through lateral cutaneous branches that pierce the deep fascia along the mid-axillary line\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ethoracoacromial artery\u003C/strong\u003E primarily supplies the deltoid and pectoralis muscles through its pectoral, clavicular, acromial and deltoid branches\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperior thoracic artery\u003C/strong\u003E is a small branch of the axillary artery that supplies the upper chest wall muscles and first two intercostal spaces\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Elateral thoracic artery\u003C/strong\u003E descends along the lateral border of pectoralis minor to supply the lateral and inferior aspects of the breast\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese vessels form an extensive anastomotic network within the breast tissue. Understanding this blood supply is crucial for breast surgery and reconstruction procedures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The internal thoracic artery provides the primary blood supply to the medial breast via perforating branches","The lateral thoracic artery supplies the lateral and inferior aspects of the breast","The posterior intercostal arteries contribute to breast blood supply via lateral cutaneous branches","The thoracoacromial artery supplies the deltoid and pectoralis muscles via its pectoral, clavicular, acromial and deltoid branches"],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57090"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17561"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57090","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57090"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-19T19:12:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-19T19:14:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10251"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71594"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4926"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiovascular","synonyms":[],"de